README
======

The agileSI Splunk app correlates, analyzes and visualizes security relevant data and events from SAP systems by the help of Splunk searches, dashboards and reports.

The SAP/Splunk integration requires the agileSI connector software, agileSI or agileSI light, to get the events into Splunk.
A free demo version of agileSI light is available via the download section on our agileSI website (http://www.agilesi.net/en/resources/)


Requirements
------------
•	"agileSI" or "agileSI light" SAP Connector/Agent software (to get the events into Splunk)
 
Installation
------------
•	Download and install the agileSI App for Splunk
•	Create and configure index(es) for your agileSI/SAP data on Splunk (optional)
•	configure inputs.conf and set the correct sourectypes (see: Forwarding your log files)
 
Forwarding your log files
-------------------------
•	Install Splunk Universal Forwarder on your system where agileSI connector (agileSI or agileSI Light) is installed
	or use the syslog function of the agileSI light connector
•	inputs.conf of your forwarder must contain the following information:
	•	Directory on the filesystem to be monitored 
	•	The correct index, you configured on the indexer
	•	Set the correct sourcetype
			For the agileSI light connector, the correct sourcetype is "agileSI"

Configuration of your Splunk system
-----------------------------------
•	The role of the agileSI user needs authorizations to the configured indexes
•	The configured index needs to be added to "Indexes searched by default" in the role of the agileSI user

Saved searches
--------------
This app includes some saved searches. 
Some of the saved searches will populate dashboard, to accelerate the dashboard.
After installing the app, it takes some time until all saved searches are run once. 
Because of this, you will get some error messages like "Error in 'SearchOperator:loadjob': Cannot find artifacts for savedsearch...".
If all saved searches were executed once, thie error messages should be disapeared.

The search "agileSI - Security incidents" will populate the summary index "summary_agilesi".
This summary index is needed for some dashboard searces. (Of course, you can customize this summary index. See: "Customizing of agileSI") 
 
Customizing of agileSI
----------------------
agileSI  comes with a lot of searches that correlate SAP data with lookup tables.
Most of them are preconfigured but the following should be maintained by the customer:
All lists are located in “$SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps/agileSI/lookups” and have the suffix “.csv”
•	agileSI-Users_in_Corporate_Directory (White list for user)
•	agileSI-Known_locations (SAP-Systems of your landscape)
•	agileSI-List_of_user_accounts_to_be_watched (Priviledged user per system-id to be watched)
•	agileSI-List_of_firefighter_accounts (List of your firefighter/emergency user per system-id)
•	agileSI-List_of_administrator_accounts (List of your basis administrators per system-id)

The summary index "summary_agilesi" has the following defaults:
• 	Data will be frozen (deleted) after 186 days (~6 month)
• 	Maximum size of this index is 5GB.
For customizing "summary_agilesi", it is recommended to create a directory named "local" inside the app directory.
Configure the custom paramater in “$SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps/agileSI/local/indexes.conf".

More information
-----------------
Learn more about the available product variants and further instructions on how to install the agileSI light connector software, on our website http://www.agilesi.net/
